The path that stands out economically is the documented “residual constituent” refund branch: mint uses only the proportional subset, then `refundDust` converts and refunds the entire leftover constituent balance. I’m checking the Basket interface and mint semantics next to see whether a two-stage call can legitimately strand value on the zapper and then over-refund it.
